descript.abstract: This raster data layer is the output of a simulation model named Sea Level Affecting Marshes Model (SLAMM) version 6.1 beta (www.warrenpinnacle.com). This is the simulated result for one specific time-step in the scenario modeled. Each raster cell value represents a vegetation category specific to the SLAMM model. Vegetation categories are described in the SLAMM 6 beta Technical Documentation.
descript.purpose: This sea level rise simulation was performed by The Nature Conservancy for a project funded by the USEPA Gulf of Mexico Program, Project Number: MX-95463410-0, "Modeling and Abating the Impacts of Sea Level Rise on Five Significant Estuarine Systems in the Gulf of Mexico".
